## Session discipline

- Cursor is the primary harness. Opus 4.8 plans/orchestrates; Composer 2.5 executes.
- Branch prefixes: `cursor/*`, `claude/*`, `feature/*`, `fix/*`. One session = one task; atomic commits.
- When you learn something durable and project-scoped, append it to `docs/memory/MEMORY.md` and update its index.

## Before you change UI code (failure-mode rules)

- **Trace structural invariants first.** Before changing shared rendering, write out what every variant/state will look like after the change. If you cannot predict it, ask — do not edit.
- **One request = one change.** Name the files you will touch; surface unrelated issues, never fold them in.
- **Verify visually before "done."** Render the change and confirm it; "it should work" is not done.

## Delivery modules (this is a website repo)

Per `arjun-ai-gems/frameworks/product-delivery/APPLICABILITY.md`, load these when the work calls for them: shaping, ship-pipeline, discovery, analytics, accessibility, performance. Specs live at `arjun-ai-gems/frameworks/product-delivery/modules/<name>.md`.

